<br>
The combat system is similar to EQ in that you hit a button to initiate an attack, but the special moves are more complicated. As you fight, you gain TP, when you reach 100 TP you can use a special attack. Every weapon has a different set of attacks. What the player needs to learn are Renkei(JP) or Skill Chains(E). When certain weapon skills are chained together and timed right, an additional effect hits the target.<br>
<br>
For example, say a dagger using character chooses to use the skill &quot;Wasp Sting&quot;, if a sword using person follows 3 seconds afterwards with the skill &quot;Burning Blade&quot;, an added effect (fire based) called liquefaction will hit the mob. It gets even more interesting when casters get in on the chain too. As soon as a caster sees the liquefaction effect, they have about 5 seconds to use a fire based spell (since liquefaction is fire) to score a magic burst, which adds alot of damage. Unless you are a red mage, spells will often take more than 5 seconds to cast. so timing is critical. A group can unleash alot of damage really fast if they know how to set up a long chain.<br>
<br>
There are also class specific skills that are on timers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hendaddy>Hendaddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/03 3:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2218.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: meh</span><hr size=1> For me the UI only took a few days to get used to and afterwards it became very simple.  I don't even use the mouse anymore and every command is only a keystroke or two away in which I completely like.<br>
